Step 1). docker run --name container-name -it ubuntu /bin/bash

Step 2). useradd -m -d /home/username /bin/bash username

Step 3). passwd username

Step 4). apt-get update

Step 5). apt-get install openssh-server

Step 6). apt-get install vim

Step 7). service ssh status

Step 9). servive ssh start or stop

Step 10). go to Souce machine and create connection between two server using below command, apply this command on both side

Step 11). ssh container username@container-ip

then transfer required files

Step 12). Enter this below command in Execute shell

sshpass -p "QA-server" scp target/LoginWebApp.war QA-server@172.17.0.3:/home/QA-server/Distros/apache-tomcat-8.5.35/webapps

 
for single server means for base machine 

cp target/abc.war username@ip:/path



